ging\neffect. The magnetic energy stored by the twisting magnetic field is converted\nto kinetic energy of the jet directly rather than propagating as an Alfven\nwave. Thus, as the rotation of the black hole becomes faster, the poloidal\nvelocity of the jet becomes faster. In the rapidly rotating black hole case the\njet-like outflow can be produced by the frame dragging effect only through the\ntwisting of magnetic field even if there is no stellar rotation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Apr 2004 06:16:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
